# 3f0dd50dbefa4732a308471f051f44fc
msgid "Open the :guilabel:`Preferences` menu in JOSM, and click on the :guilabel:`Plugins` tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/beginner/osm/107-imagery-offset.rst:253
# 9db54d060bde4fba807532a359308791
msgid "Find the plugin named *“imagery_offset_db”* and check the box next to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/beginner/osm/107-imagery-offset.rst:258
# f041eec58c644f18af9fbf82a74057bb
msgid "Click :guilabel:`OK`.  You will need to restart JOSM to finish the plugin installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/beginner/osm/107-imagery-offset.rst:261
# fd3c0750d04d4259b4ae221c0e4a3c8c
msgid "In the same way that you are able to save offsets as bookmarks, this plugin allows you to save offsets to a central database, and to access the offsets that other users have created.  Hence, if one mapper creates an imagery offset in an area, other users can use the exact same offset to map with."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/beginner/osm/107-imagery-offset.rst:267
# 6b32aa5ddcdf46cf8494a4cacee65121
msgid "When using aerial imagery layers, you should ALWAYS check for existing offsets, and when you create your own offset, you should ALWAYS save it to this database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/beginner/osm/107-imagery-offset.rst:271
